// runtime/stdlib/into_iterator.kara
//
// CR-202 slice 6.2d. Per design.md § Iteration — `IntoIterator`
// is the trait that drives `for x in collection` loops. `IntoIter`
// is the iterator type returned by `into_iter()`; `Item` is the
// element type that iterator yields. Two associated types because
// the for-loop expansion needs both: `IntoIter` for the loop
// variable's static type, `Item` for the element binding.

trait IntoIterator {
    type Item;
    type IntoIter;
}
